subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
paratype
)

(
Fig. 38
). Basal piece slightly longer than wide, parallel-sided, dorsally open, basally rounded; remaining parts elongate, strongly constricted laterally at base of parameres, apically lobed; median lobe short and spatulate, apically rounded, narrowly bifid; parameres elongate, apically unsclerotized, with a triangular lateral tooth near base.
